          new members)</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist></para>

    <section>
      <title>Opening and ADMIN</title>

      <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->The
      check-in for this meeting is the same as always: how are you? Most
      likely, everyone has had a busy day, so make sure to slow down and
      arrive and be present.</para>

      <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->The
      ADMIN phase is now relevant in full. I am repeating some slightly
      changed info so that you have it all in one spot:</para>

      <para><variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><emphasis role="bold">Attendance.</emphasis></term>

            <listitem>
              <para><itemizedlist>
                  <listitem>
                    <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Who
                    is here, who is not? Who said they wouldn’t make it, or
                    they’d be late?</para>
                  </listitem>

                  <listitem>
                    <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Make
                    sure all the meeting-related roles are filled. Ask someone
                    to take notes until you select a secretary.</para>
                  </listitem>

                  <listitem>
                    <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->You
                    are again facilitating by default. Ask for consent to
                    continue just for a few minutes until you have your
                    official facilitator.</para>
                  </listitem>
                </itemizedlist></para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><emphasis role="bold">Duration.</emphasis></term>

            <listitem>
              <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Set
              an expectation of how long you expect the meeting to be. The
              plan is set up for 120 minutes. Some people might tell you they
              are leaving early.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><emphasis role="bold">Minutes.</emphasis></term>

            <listitem>
              <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Have
              the minutes been distributed? Did everyone receive them? (For
              example, did any emails bounce, etc.?) Is there consent to the
              minutes? An objection to the minutes would mean that something
              in the minutes is an inaccurate representation of what others
              perceived in the meeting. This is rare and so this should not
              take long. Find consent and move on.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><emphasis role="bold">Information.</emphasis></term>

            <listitem>
              <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Ask
              if anyone has any announcements they want to share now.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><emphasis role="bold">Next meeting.</emphasis></term>

            <listitem>
              <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Maybe
              your group already has another meeting set up? If so, remind
              everyone when that is. If not, schedule a meeting now or assign
              the task to someone in the group.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->If
      any topic here sparks a discussion, either put the topic on the agenda
      or note it for later.</para>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Consent to agenda</title>

      <para>Present the agenda as laid out in this chapter (and in the summary
      table at the end of this chapter). Make sure people know enough to make
      an informed decision and ask for consent.</para>

      <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->(While
      you are following a template, there might be reasons to adjust the
      agenda with additions or modifications. Note that if you’re short on
      time or run out of time, today’s last two agenda items can be moved to
      next time.)</para>
    </section>

    <section xml:id="roledescriptions">
      <title>Selecting roles</title>

      <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->The
      first agenda item will be to select people into the three roles:</para>

      <para><itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
            <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->leader
            (or use the term <emphasis
            role="from-text">coordinator</emphasis><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->)</para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->facilitator</para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->secretary</para>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Having
      those roles will make it easier for the circle to operate. Choosing the
      people who serve in those roles with intentionality will support equal
      consideration of <!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->everyone’s<!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->
      needs and trust.</para>

      <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->(Note:
      sociocracy’s 4th standard role, the delegate which links to the parent
      circle, is not needed in a one-circle organization because there is no
      circle to link to.)</para>

      <informaltable>
        <!--Warning: passing through `tabular` element: -->

        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><!--Warning: passing through `p` element: --><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->darkerteal
            <emphasis role="bold">Role</emphasis></td>

            <td><!--Warning: passing through `p` element: --><emphasis
            role="bold">Activities</emphasis></td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td><!--Warning: passing through `p` element: --><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" -->Leader</td>

            <td><!--Warning: passing through `p` element: --><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" --><para>Making
            sure the circle is operating.</para> <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                  <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Checking
                  in with people and tasks</para>
                </listitem>

                <listitem>
                  <para><!--Warning: text element with unused attributes: color="#000000" fontsize="90%" -->Serving
                  as ‘catch-all’ that notices items that are falling through
